  "prompt": "Is it a crime thing to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious criminal offense. It involves illegally obtaining money and making it appear to have come from a legitimate source. Money laundering typically involves three steps:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of the money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Making the money appear legal and usable\n\nMoney laundering is illegal in most countries and can result in:\n- Heavy fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal prosecution\n\nIt's often associated with other crimes like drug trafficking, fraud, and organized crime.",
